reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought around Black Friday and can say the price is very good.Pros:- Fans are preinstalled. Saves you a good bit of work.- Fans have RGB lights, making the pc look much more aesthetically pleasing.- Enough room for all components.Cons:Have not found any yet!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Used this to build my first gaming pc. Packaged really good. Did not come damaged. Has 6 preinstalled fans. Love it and it was inexpensive

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice Midsize case only wish it was 20mm longer so full size PSU and HDD cage would both fit.
reviews.reviewText: Nice little case, just wish it was a little longer. XFX Speedster SWFT309 AMD Radeon RX 6700 XT CORE Gaming and Corsair RM1000x (2021) Fully Modular ATX Power Supply both fit nicely however I had to remove the HDD cage to make room for the cables. There was still room for 3 Samsung SSD 870 QVO's. Fans are super quiet and the ARGB works great. The door can be a challenge to put on the hinge pins. A staggered arrangement would have cured that. Mine is in a tight location so the door is really tough to get back on the pins unless you can open the door quite wide. For the Money, it's pretty darn hard to beat this case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. The cases are decent looking, Good airflow/Lots of mesh. Assembly is quick since they already did the fans for ya. Only complaints is the fan bearing quality sometimes they are doa or go out fast on one of em and can grind loud but for under 100$ can't complain much for thatMost RGB fans are 7-20 $ each and ya get 6 so essentially the case costs 30-40$ really vs buying a case and fans separate and these allow addressable rgb Ive bought 5 musetex cases so I can say this review is pretty accurate over all the buys(I build pcs and stay in touch with owners ) pics of different versions of there cases included!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Decent product for the price. It's the perfect size to fit between the legs of my ikea table (Linnmon). This was my first build and the cable management was very easy. The case provides a great airflow from the front, top and back. The glass window is also a great touch. The included 6 fans are not the best or the quietest but are definitely welcomed. At least they're less noisy than my laptop lol.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Case, fully recommend, great value for $$
reviews.reviewText: Case comes with fans pre installed, you need to connect the seperate fan control board to your motherboard.Lots of space, you CAN fit larger PSU than they say is the maximum length by removing the HDD bay, which I did, because it’s 2022.ATX boards will likely require you to remove one of the fans to install, it’s easy and really no problem.Hold down the RGB button for a few seconds and then you can click it to cycle through the modes, there are a bunch.Noctua fan barely fitAnother reviewer is correct about the top being kind of flimsy, but just don’t put anything heavy on your PC case lolAll in all pretty good case. decent airflow as far as I can tell. Will come back and update if there are any problems

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Case, Great Airflow.
reviews.reviewText: This is a great case to build in. Plenty of room for it’s size to fit the larger graphics cards on the market with 350mm max length.The airflow is terrific. I don’t see temps over 70c for my 6950xt GPU or 5800X3D CPU during game play. Barely sees mid 80s during stress tests.Only minor knock on this case is rear cable management. It’s average and could use some more tie down points, but this is a very very minor complaint.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful computer case!
reviews.reviewText: I got this case to build my own computer and I am in love with it. It is not too small or too big. Everything you need is on this. I installed the fans you see in the picture and I am so happy with it. The door to the case opens very easily to clean and exchange parts. I like this case so much my plan is to buy another one and create a computer for my husband.

After having the case for 6 months, all of us sudden the rgb and the fans stopped working. Giving more power to the fans from your bios turns them back on but then you can't control the color of them( I think its a fan controller issue) . I loved the case before hand, but now I'm iffy on it
